<subSubSection id="BBE492D54A9AB006E80E483DA9F1CD07" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="68605DF65DD631ACD549BE7D31BA0837" pageNumber="205">
SANTSCHI avait decrit cette forme comme race du 
<taxonomicName id="4FAEBFBD5889F495548F31358A3F186D" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:138840" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Ponera jeanneli Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jeanneli">P. jeanneli</taxonomicName>
SANT. du Kenya et du Ruwenzori. Examinant les types dans sa collection, je crois necessaire d'elever 
<taxonomicName id="8B56887283661E31BA6DBCFC64DDFA60" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:142097" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Ponera abyssinica GuA©rin-MA©neville" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abyssinica">abyssinica</taxonomicName>
au rang d'espece, vu ses differences de clypeus et de thorax avec 
<taxonomicName id="7AEE2F7FF0829FCBDE3AFB90E92052F0" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:138840" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Ponera jeanneli Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jeanneli">jeanneli</taxonomicName>
. Les [[worker]] du Nimba sont identiques aux types d'Abyssinie, a part leur tete un peu plus luisante; elles sont brunes et aveugles, d'aspect rappelant 
<taxonomicName id="F998D6C87172FFA6F5328B13432453BD" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:138802" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Ponera dulcis Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dulcis">P. dulcis</taxonomicName>
, mais la comparaison des fig. j et l (fig. 3) donnera les differences essentielles; en outre, 
<taxonomicName id="CD0C2D61FC14683B6BCC6D258D497261" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:142097" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Ponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Ponera abyssinica GuA©rin-MA©neville" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abyssinica">abyssinica</taxonomicName>
est un 
<taxonomicName id="2875BC460C654CAEF9619A71C574A765" LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:24837" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Hypoponera" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-HNS="Hypoponera Santschi" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="205" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Hypoponera</taxonomicName>
, sans sillon dorsal entre mesoet epinotum.
</paragraph>
